Text Content: Designed for use in kitchens and furnace rooms, they reduce nuisance alarms caused by cooking fumes or high humidity. These FireX smoke alarms should be placed in single-family households or in each individual living unit of multiple-family buildings. All smoke alarms should be replaced every 10 years. With state-of-the-art production testing equipment and installer focused innovations, FireX products have earned their reputation as the most preferred alarms among contractors. 480 484 4480

Text Content: Features and Benefits Advanced photoelectric design –  Fast detection of slow, smoldering fires. Installation design and features similar to other FireX smoke alarms –  Contractor familiarity with installation. Interconnects with most FireX smoke, carbon monoxide and heat alarms –  Compatible with other contractor preferred FireX products (except item 480). Lighted Power/Alarm LED –  Confirms unit is receiving power and provides visual indication of ini- tiating alarm in interconnected systems.
